  "narrative": "<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Short impact summary</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">This software tool, released in 2024 by Bernadeta Dadonaite, Jesse Bloom, Will Hannon, and a collaborator, provides the computational pipeline underlying a deep mutational scanning (DMS) study of the H5N1 influenza hemagglutinin from a 2021 American Wigeon isolate. Archived on Zenodo with a citable DOI, it has recorded 46 downloads and 155 views, and has been referenced in a peer-reviewed PLOS Biology article, marking its entry into the biomedical literature.</p>\n\n<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Full narrative</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">The tool represents the versioned, published release of the <em>dms-vep</em> pipeline configured specifically for deep mutational scanning of the H5N1 hemagglutinin gene from an American Wigeon strain collected in South Carolina in 2021. Deep mutational scanning is a high-throughput experimental approach that systematically measures how every possible amino acid substitution in a viral protein affects its function, offering a comprehensive map of mutational tolerance and potential escape from antibody or antiviral pressure.",
